<h1>Sample Pooling</h1>
<ul>
</ul>
<h3>Defining a sample pooling step</h3>
<ol>
  <li>As admin, log on to the protocol admin page.</li>
  <li>Either select an existing protocol or create a new protocol for
the pooling step.</li>
  <li>In the screen that accepts inputs for a protocol step:</li>
  <ul>
    <li>Select the 'Pool' radio button in the Step Name section</li>
    <li>Select the target container type from the popup menu.&nbsp;
Right now only tubes are supported.</li>
    <li>Check the 'Scanner View Enabled' checkbox</li>
    <img src="$Help_Image_dir/Pooling_Step_Setup.png">
  </ul>
  <li>Save the step. Note that the step name will be automatically generated.<br>
  </li>
</ol>
<h3>Going through a sample pooling step</h3>
<ol>
  <li>Scan in the source tubes that are to be pooled.</li>
  <li>Save the tubes as a tube set.</li>
  <li>Select the protocol that contains the pooling step.</li>
  <li>In the pooling step page, enter the amounts to pooled from for
each source tubes.</li>
  <img src="$Help_Image_dir/Pooling_Step_Usage.png"> <li>A new
original tube will be created along with a barcode.</li>
  <li>The protocol will continue with the next step.<br>
  </li>
</ol>
<h3>Viewing pooling ancestry</h3>
<ol>
  <li>After the pooling is done, its ancestry can be viewed from the
scan tubes home page.</li>
  <ul>
    <li>Scan in one of the source tubes:</li>
    <img src="$Help_Image_dir/Pooling_To_Ancestry.png"> <li>Scan in
the target tube:<br>
    </li>
    <img src="$Help_Image_dir/Pooling_From_Ancestry.png">
  </ul>
</ol>